## 🏥 5-Step MedSpa SEO Audit Workflow

### Step 1: Technical Foundation Scan
```
CHECKLIST:
□ robots.txt allows critical paths
□ XML sitemap submitted and valid
□ Page speed: LCP < 2.5s, FID < 100ms, CLS < 0.1
□ Mobile-first responsive design verified
□ HTTPS with valid certificate
□ Canonical tags on all pages
□ No duplicate content / thin pages
□ Internal linking structure (max 3 clicks to any page)
□ 404 errors resolved
□ Structured data validates in Schema.org validator

TOOLS: Google PageSpeed Insights, Screaming Frog, Schema Validator
OUTPUT: Technical health score (0-100) + priority fix list
```

### Step 2: Local SEO & GBP Optimization
```
CHECKLIST:
□ Google Business Profile claimed & verified
□ NAP consistency (Name, Address, Phone) across all directories
□ Primary category: "Medical Spa" (or most specific available)
□ Secondary categories added (3-5 relevant)
□ Business description keyword-optimized (750 chars)
□ Services listed with descriptions and prices
□ Photos: 10+ high-quality (storefront, interior, staff, results)
□ Google Posts: weekly frequency
□ Q&A section populated (seed 10+ questions)
□ Review velocity: strategy for 5+ reviews/month
□ Citation consistency across 40+ directories

TOOLS: BrightLocal, Moz Local, GBP Dashboard
OUTPUT: Local visibility score + citation gap report
```

### Step 3: Content & Keyword Architecture
```
CHECKLIST:
□ Treatment pages for every service offered
□ Location pages for service areas (city + neighborhood)
□ Blog/resource hub with educational content
□ Keyword mapping: 1 primary + 2-3 secondary per page
□ Search intent alignment (informational vs transactional)
□ Content depth: 1,500+ words on treatment pages
□ Internal linking between related treatments
□ Before/after galleries (with alt text)
□ Video content embedded (consultations, procedures)
□ FAQ section on every treatment page (feeds FAQ schema)

KEYWORD PRIORITIES:
- "[Treatment] + [City]" — transactional (highest priority)
- "[Treatment] cost/price" — transactional
- "[Treatment] before and after" — consideration
- "Best [treatment] near me" — transactional
- "Is [treatment] worth it" — informational
- "[Treatment] vs [alternative]" — consideration

OUTPUT: Content calendar + keyword gap analysis
```

### Step 4: AI-Ready Structured Data Deployment
```
CHECKLIST:
□ LocalBusiness/MedicalBusiness schema on homepage
□ Service schema on each treatment page
□ FAQPage schema on FAQ sections
□ Review/AggregateRating schema
□ Breadcrumb schema on all pages
□ HowTo schema on procedure pages
□ Event schema for promotions/specials
□ Person schema for practitioners (with credentials)
□ ImageObject schema on before/after galleries
□ VideoObject schema on embedded videos

VALIDATION:
- Google Rich Results Test: all schemas pass
- Schema.org validator: no errors
- Test with "site:[domain]" — rich snippets appearing?
- Test in ChatGPT/Perplexity — is business information surfaced?

OUTPUT: Schema deployment report + validation screenshots
```

### Step 5: Authority & Off-Page Signals
```
CHECKLIST:
□ Backlink profile audit (toxic link disavow)
□ Local link building: chamber of commerce, local press
□ Industry directories: RealSelf, Healthgrades, Zocdoc
□ Content partnerships: local influencers, wellness blogs
□ Social signals: active profiles linked to site
□ Brand mentions monitoring
□ Competitor backlink gap analysis
□ Digital PR opportunities identified
□ Patient testimonial acquisition workflow
□ Monthly reporting cadence established

METRICS TO TRACK:
- Domain Authority / Domain Rating
- Referring domains (growth rate)
- Organic traffic (branded vs non-branded)
- Local pack rankings (top 3 keywords)
- Conversion rate: visitor → lead
- Cost per lead (organic channel)
- Review velocity and average rating
- AI citation frequency (Perplexity, ChatGPT mentions)

OUTPUT: Authority building roadmap + 90-day link targets
```

---

## 🎯 AI-First Content Principles

### Writing for Machines AND Humans
1. **Lead with facts** — AI extracts structured claims first
2. **Use specific numbers** — "$3,200 average treatment" not "affordable"
3. **Answer questions directly** — First sentence = answer, then elaborate
4. **Structured formatting** — Headers, lists, tables > walls of text
5. **Entity clarity** — Full name on first reference, consistent throughout
6. **Temporal markers** — "As of June 2026" helps AI assess freshness
7. **Source attribution** — Link to studies, certifications, credentials
8. **Outcome framing** — Results-first language in every description

### Machine-Readable Signals Checklist
- [ ] Every page has at least ONE JSON-LD schema block
- [ ] All images have descriptive alt text (not keyword stuffed)
- [ ] Tables use proper HTML <table> markup
- [ ] Lists use semantic <ul>/<ol> markup
- [ ] Headings follow strict hierarchy (H1 → H2 → H3)
- [ ] Phone numbers use tel: links
- [ ] Addresses use consistent formatting
- [ ] Prices displayed in standardized format ($X,XXX)
- [ ] Hours displayed in ISO 8601 where possible

---

## 🚫 Anti-Patterns (Never Do)

1. Keyword stuffing — AI models penalize unnatural density
2. Thin content pages — merge or expand below 500 words
3. Missing schemas — every page needs structured data
4. Inconsistent NAP — single discrepancy breaks local trust
5. Ignoring AI citations — monitor Perplexity/ChatGPT mentions
6. Stock photography without context — reduces E-E-A-T signals
7. Hidden text/links — instant penalty territory
8. Duplicate GMB listings — merge or remove

---

## 🔧 Integration Notes

Deploy JSON-LD in the <head> section of each page. For Next.js/React apps, use the `next-seo` package or custom `<Script type="application/ld+json">` components. Validate all schemas before deploying with Google's Rich Results Test.
